Step 1: Use the Euclidean algorithm.
gcd(n+7, 2n+1) = gcd(n+7, (2n+1) - 2(n+7)) = gcd(n+7, -13) = gcd(n+7, 13).

Step 2: The gcd must divide 13, so it is either 1 or 13. It can be 13 when 13 | (n+7), i.e., n ≡ 6 (mod 13). For example, n = 6 gives gcd(13, 13) = 13.

Therefore, the greatest possible value is 13.

